  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Hi,\r\n\r\nWe would like to use the txpool API in order to check pending status of orders submitted through our Geth cluster. I have a couple of questions about txpool:\r\n\r\n1) Are there any inherent dangers of running a public Geth node w/ the txpool RPC API enabled?\r\n2) If we submit a transaction to a node and txpool is enabled, does information about that transaction become instantly available to that node? What about other nodes? How long would it take before other nodes became aware of the transaction?\r\n3) Is there any performance overhead to having the txpool API enabled (other than I/O when querying), or does it simply allow access to existing data structures already present in Geth?\r\n\r\nI searched and couldn't find detailed documentation about the Txpool. Please feel free to drop any links that might be helpful in gaining a deeper understanding of this feature. Thanks!",
