    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "The `txpool` API is only an accessor to the local transaction pool within your Geth instance. Submitting a transaction does not change whether you enable this API or not, it's just an exploratory endpoint\r\n\r\nIn theory there are no dangers of exposing this API. In practice the Geth APIs are not throttled or rate limited, so open RPC access can most probably DOS the node simply by constantly requesting data with high IO or CPU overhead.\r\n\r\nAny particular reason though you'd like to expose it publicly?",
